t fundamental concerns are as urgent now as they were in 1516 when it was written. Clarence H. Miller's wonderful translation of More's classic is now happily once again available to readers. This is the English edition that best captures the tone and texture of More's original Latin, and its notes and introduction, along with the lively afterward by Jerry Harp, graciously supply exactly the kinds of help a modern reader might desire.”-David Scott Kastan, Yale University  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aElectronic books. 0aUtopiasvEarly works to 1800. 0aUtopias. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Movements / Humanism.2bisacsh1 aHarp, Jerry, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMiller, Clarence H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z97831106725030 cprintz978030018610940uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030019522440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300195224423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300195224/original  a978-3-11-067250-3  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY